1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:03,000
- When Dad tried to win your heart,
what did he do?

2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:04,760
- Your dad often patted me on my butt.

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:05,640
- Huh?

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,040
- Why are you patting on my butt?

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:11,320
- It’s covered with sand.

6
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:12,640
- Don’t pat on my butt.

7
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:15,760
- Can you tell what I’m thinking right now?

8
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:17,320
- You’re getting too close.

9
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:21,960
- Are you crossing the line?

10
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:23,640
- You crossed it first last night.

11
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:33,800
August, what volume are you up to
in the manga?

12
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:34,560
Volume 30.

13
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:35,040
What about you?

14
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,200
Volume 39.

15
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:38,800
Guys, I’m here.

16
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:40,760
How are the photos, Achi?

17
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:45,360
Let me see.

18
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:48,360
Achi, your face looks so funny in this picture.

19
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,240
You look dumbfounded.

20
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,920
(The photo album is a sign that…)

21
00:00:54,200 --> 00:01:01,360
(the carefree days of childhood are slowly turning into the journey of adulthood.)

22
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:08,080
(We want to cherish this happiness
while it lasts.)

23
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:10,840
(The charm of a film camera is that…)

24
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:15,080
(the most outtake photo is taken
when we had the biggest laugh.)

25
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,000
(Each photo can be taken only once.)

26
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:24,640
(It’s the first time we wore colorful clothes
that we’d never wear again.)

27
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:29,280
(It’s the first time we stole our dad’s wax
to copy our favorite celebrity’s hairstyle.)

28
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:34,440
(It’s the first time we wore our favorite shoes
and walked out with confidence.)

29
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:38,400
(It’s the first time
we did many crazy things together.)

30
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,480
(It’s also the first time…)

31
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:49,240
(that we experienced love.)

32
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,360
Augar, look.

33
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,920
You look so funny in this photo.

34
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,640
Stop it, Achi.

35
00:02:59,200 --> 00:02:59,880
Guys.

36
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,880
I have something to show you today.

37
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,440
What is it?

38
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:11,240
Now, I have my own phone.

39
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,400
I also have one.

40
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,240
Me too.

41
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:22,720
My phone is a newer model.

42
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,840
I also got a new phone.

43
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:27,160
My mom gave my old phone
to our house helper.

44
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,520
Now, this is brag-worthy.

45
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,560
Why do your phones look so good?

46
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,840
Your phone is an older model.

47
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,360
This is not cool.

48
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,560
But it’s okay.

49
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:44,240
At least it’s more convenient
to contact you guys now.

50
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:46,320
Good. I won’t feel lonely now.

51
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:49,600
When I was the only one who had a phone,
I had no one to call.

52
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,280
Are you trying to flex on us?

53
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:54,560
Hey.

54
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,240
Let’s exchange our numbers.

55
00:03:57,840 --> 00:04:01,000
Ko Neung and Ko Song,
you don’t have to do that.

56
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,600
You are living next door to each other.

57
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,600
You guys hang out every day.

58
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,600
You’re so damn annoying.

59
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,960
Of course,
we need to have each other’s numbers.

60
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,240
In case of an emergency.

61
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,800
Did any of you get the postcard that we sent?

62
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,720
What do you mean?

63
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,680
How are we going to get it?

64
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,360
Didn’t we send it to someone else?

65
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:37,920
I mean…

66
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:44,240
What Ko Song means is that
if we wrote it to our future selves.

67
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,520
Right?

68
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,120
I wrote to myself.

69
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:49,560
Me too.

70
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,640
See? We all wrote to ourselves.

71
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,200
Are you sure?

72
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,520
What did you write to yourself?

73
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,040
It’s none of your business.

74
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,720
I can write whatever I want.

75
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,440
Don’t be so nosy.

76
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,880
Are you having a secret with me?

77
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,520
You guys are having a secret with me, right?

78
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,640
August, if you are saying this,
doesn’t it mean you didn’t write to yourself?

79
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,160
Tell us who you wrote it to.

80
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,880
Who did you write it to?

81
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:25,080
I wrote to my parents.

82
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:28,120
I wrote to wish them good health.

83
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,160
Ptooey!

84
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,400
Did you write a birthday card?

85
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,480
I don’t believe you.

86
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,320
It’s obvious that you are lying, August.

87
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,800
This is odd.

88
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,280
Are you flirting with a girl without telling me?

89
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,880
August.

90
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,720
You guys are ganging up on me.

91
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,920
You guys are in a relationship.

92
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,720
August, what the hell are you saying?

93
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,280
Ouch.

94
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,240
Hey!

95
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,040
Little boy, get in.

96
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,680
Augar, do you know how to drive?

97
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:12,640
Sure.

98
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,440
What is this?

99
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,320
Ko Neung, get in.

100
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,000
Augar.

101
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,240
Do you know how to drive?

102
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,680
Sure.

103
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,960
Ko Song, get in.

104
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,720
Augar, do you know how to drive?

105
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:35,000
Sure.

106
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,160
So now we can take a trip, right?

107
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:41,560
We can take a trip without any worries.

108
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,840
That’s right, Achi.

109
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,640
Do you want to go to Bangkok?

110
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,120
I can show you around the city.

111
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:49,240
The kid from Bangkok is showing off.

112
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,840
I mean it.

113
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,360
I want to go to Chiang Mai.

114
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,200
My dad has a house there.

115
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:54,800
Do you want to go?

116
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,640
This is a real example of showing off.

117
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,680
Why didn’t August come with you?

118
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,640
He wasn’t home.

119
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,920
Augar, where do you want to go?

120
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,520
Yes, where do you intend to go?

121
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,120
No.

122
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:22,040
Where are you taking us?

123
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,920
I just want to go for a drive.

124
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:26,800
Why?

125
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,360
Don’t you have a destination in mind?

126
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,280
Augar, you are going quite slow?

127
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,720
Your speed is only 60 km per hour.

128
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,280
We are not in a rush, right?

129
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,400
What’s wrong, Augar?

130
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,720
The weather is not hot.

131
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,800
Are you sick?

132
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,800
Why are you unusually quiet?

133
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,600
I want you guys to be my witness.

134
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:58,880
For what?

135
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,040
This is my first time driving.

136
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,240
How is it?

137
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,840
You don’t mind it, right?

138
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,920
Thanks for trusting me.

139
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,800
Stop talking and
just pay attention to the road.

140
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,840
I get it.

141
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,440
But I have my driving license.

142
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,280
Augar!

143
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,600
Here.

144
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,200
Thanks.

145
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,240
Can I eat it?

146
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,720
Or do I have to do something first?

147
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,480
You can eat it.

148
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,680
Okay.

149
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:42,440
Right, I received it.

150
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,520
I got it this morning.

151
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,600
Why did you bring it with you?

152
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,280
Someone might see it.

153
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:52,400
Even if they see it,
they won’t know who wrote it anyway.

154
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,680
We finally get to go out together.

155
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,000
Yeah.

156
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:12,520
We were in Grade 10
when you sent me the first note, right?

157
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,480
Do you still have it?

158
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,840
I’m not sure.

159
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,160
It’s probably in my book box.

160
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,640
Please don’t let him find it. Amen.

161
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,360
It’s embarrassing.

162
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:36,200
It’s been so long. Two years.

163
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:44,680
If someone sees us together,
won’t they be confused?

164
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:50,800
I don’t think we will run into anyone.

165
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,000
Augar, damn it. Pull over.

166
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:02,920
What the hell is going on?

167
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,520
August, help me.

168
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,520
I almost died.

169
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,080
What are you doing here?

170
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:18,080
What are you two doing here?

171
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:22,680
So this is where you’ve been all this time.

172
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,240
August, why are you with Tle?

173
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,720
Oh, that’s the postcard that you wrote.

174
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:34,280
Yes, I remember it.

175
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,760
No, it’s not.

176
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,560
Are the two of them…

177
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,600
Nonsense.

178
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,840
Let me see it.

179
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,480
No.

180
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,240
Let me see it.

181
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,440
Tle, take it.

182
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,720
Tle, let me see it.

183
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,400
Give it to me.

184
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,120
Good job, Ko.

185
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,360
I was about to read it.

186
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,520
Run.

187
00:10:59,200 --> 00:10:59,680
Tle.

188
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,800
Hey.

189
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,160
Tle.

190
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:07,840
When will they stop acting childishly?

191
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,280
What did you bring?

192
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:30,600
Wow! It looks tasty.

193
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:35,200
This is the first time
that we hang out in your yard.

194
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,680
It has a full view of the orange tree.

195
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,280
It’s so refreshing.

196
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,680
You must really like it.

197
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,800
Seriously.

198
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:04,920
It’s so delicious.

199
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,440
I don’t want someone here to feel left out.

200
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:23,200
It’s unbelievable
that August and Tle are dating.

201
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:26,920
One of them is a bookworm
while the other is a manga fanatic.

202
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,640
How do you know that they are dating?

203
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,160
They might still be flirting.

204
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,520
Tle has flirted with him for a long time.

205
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:36,160
He has sent notes to him since Grade 10.

206
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,800
It’s so cool.

207
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,560
What about us?

208
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,440
Are we dating?

209
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:58,720
What is this?

210
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,480
Why are you suddenly asking me this?

211
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,000
Probably yes.

212
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,840
Can you answer it seriously?

213
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,440
Yes, we are dating.

214
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,640
I’ll be right back.

215
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:38,440
What should we call each other?

216
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:41,840
Baby, babe, sweetie, darling?

217
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,680
So cheesy.

218
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:00,760
What is this?

219
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,680
Did you make it?

220
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:11,480
Do you like it?

221
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:13,320
Very much.

222
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,040
This one is mine, and that one is yours.

223
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,400
You can use it to store whatever you want.

224
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:26,920
Do you mean our things?

225
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,560
It’s up to you.

226
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,760
The box is not big. What can I put in it?

227
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,160
Who says it’s not big?

228
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,040
Look.

229
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:47,680
I can put the moon in it.

230
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,320
You are getting good.

231
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,520
Where did you learn the pickup line?

232
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:03,560
Then I’ll use this box to store the sun.

233
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,680
I’ll feed my boyfriend.

234
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,640
Your boyfriend wants to feed you too.

235
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,280
It’s so refreshing.

236
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:38,200
Why is your hair this color?

237
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,520
Hello, Mr. Kong.

238
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,240
You.

239
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,040
Why is your hair so long?

240
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:50,080
You dyed your hair.

241
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:50,880
You keep your hair too long.

242
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,160
Fix it before next week.

243
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,000
Doesn’t it feel like watching yourself?

244
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,400
Let’s go to the classroom.

245
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:16,200
Hello, I’m Buntham Pongsuwan.

246
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,280
I’m 16.

247
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:18,400
Nice to meet you.

248
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,040
Your seat is in the back.

249
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:23,800
Hey.

250
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,080
Doesn’t it feel like watching yourself?

251
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:42,200
Mine is longer than yours.

252
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,200
I’ll catch up with you soon.

253
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,000
Don’t get too cocky.

254
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:50,000
You can’t compete with me, boy.

255
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,600
Hey.

256
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:54,280
Look, the game is over.

257
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,640
Sorry.

258
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,680
Don’t say you’re sorry.

259
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,320
Sorry.

260
00:16:58,520 --> 00:16:59,560
You are not sorry.

261
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,760
I’ve read up to volume 33.

262
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:03,400
What?

263
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,640
Damn, you are so fast.

264
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,320
It’s quite fun.

265
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,480
True.

266
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,200
August, when is the contest?

267
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,160
Next two weeks.

268
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:18,440
Are you nervous?

269
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,200
You will be the ultimate fan of Dragon Ball.

270
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,320
It will not be easy.

271
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,680
Many people apply to join the contest.

272
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:28,720
Augar.

273
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,320
Did you drive to school today?

274
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,080
Are you trying to get on my nerves?

275
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,760
Are you going to try out
for the national youth team?

276
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,480
Of course.

277
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:43,480
If I get on the team,
you have to come and watch my game.

278
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:46,440
Fine, I’ll pray to the deity
to help you make the team.

279
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:50,080
Shall we promise the deity that
we will repay him with 9,999 boiled eggs?

280
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:51,400
So you can make the team in one try.

281
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,440
Stop it, Achi.

282
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,920
Chickens cannot lay that many eggs.

283
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,360
Stop it, both of you.

284
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,120
You don’t need to pray to the deity.

285
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,520
Believe in me.

286
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:02,720
I’ve got skills.

287
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:03,840
False skills.

288
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,160
I still remember your driving skills.

289
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,760
Your driving was freaking scary.

290
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,520
Then don’t ride in my car again.

291
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,440
Where have you been?

292
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:13,680
I went to talk to scholarship students.

293
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:16,200
They said that college seniors will come
to introduce their faculties.

294
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,320
There will be seniors from a med school.

295
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:24,040
Also, seniors from Communication Arts, Engineering, and Sport Science faculties.

296
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:25,760
What faculty are you interested in?

297
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,280
Ko Song is interested in med school.

298
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,200
What about you, Achi?

299
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,400
What do you want to study?

300
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,800
My mom wants me to attend a med school.

301
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:33,760
But I’m interested in sport science.

302
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:39,400
Are you interested in sport science
or an athlete?

303
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:42,000
Are you planning
to take care of a basketball athlete?

304
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,960
Assh*le, shut your mouth with it.

305
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,160
Damn it, Augar.

306
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:50,280
Ko.

307
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,440
Can I borrow your phone?

308
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,120
Just take it out.

309
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:59,640
You can’t let teachers see it.

310
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:17,600
You are smiling.

311
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,280
You like it, don’t you?

312
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:24,240
Who permits you to change it?

313
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:25,800
What?

314
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:31,320
My number is saved as Orange.

315
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:35,160
Your number is saved as Orange’s owner.

316
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,160
Why?

317
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:43,800
Are you feeling shy, Orange’s owner?

318
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:55,960
Hello, everyone.

319
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:59,480
Please join the group of the faculty
that you are interested in.

320
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,480
Let’s go.

321
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:11,720
I believe that you are here
because you are interested in med school.

322
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:15,680
I have questions for you.
How many years does a medical degree take?

323
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,680
-Seven years.
-Six years.

324
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,040
That’s right.

325
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,000
How many bones are in the human body?

326
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:21,760
206 bones.

327
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:22,640
Correct.

328
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,520
How many bones are in the human spine?

329
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,480
26 bones.

330
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,800
You must have studied it.

331
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:38,840
We will draft a plan for a two-storey house.

332
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,040
You’ve got a good build.

333
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,600
What sport do you play?

334
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:42,600
Basketball.

335
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,640
What do you want to be?

336
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,320
A national athlete.

337
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:49,200
Then you came to the right place.

338
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
In the next activity, I need a volunteer.

339
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:54,800
Can you be the volunteer?

340
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:07,240
You will be working on a set of a film,
a drama, or a commercial ad.

341
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:11,880
Many activities are waiting for you
if you study communication arts.

342
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,560
Hold it like this.

343
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,520
Does any of you want to study in the field?

344
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:36,240
Please join us
at the Faculty of Communication Arts.

345
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,080
I have basketball practice.

346
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,000
I’ll be back.

347
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,040
Alright.

348
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,840
What’s wrong, Boss Ko?

349
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,880
I’m bored. This is not fun.

350
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,800
None of these faculties is interesting.

351
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:21,720
None of these faculties is interesting?

352
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:25,520
Or you aren’t interested
in any of these faculties?

353
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,000
No.

354
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:33,200
Does it upset you when you see it?

355
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,480
You feel uneasy when you see it, right?

356
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:39,480
You want to walk to him and grab his collar.

357
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,600
You are imagining things.

358
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:45,480
I can tell from the look on your face.

359
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,640
I think I’m right on this.

360
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,440
What about you and Tle?

361
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:54,320
Will Tle choose to attend med school
like Ko Song?

362
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,040
Yeah, I think so.

363
00:22:59,400 --> 00:22:59,960
Why?

364
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:05,040
Aren’t you worried
about being apart from him?

365
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,800
I’ve never thought about that.

366
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,280
Why are you thinking about it?

367
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,240
Excuse me.

368
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,400
What are you two doing?

369
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:33,160
Damn. It looks good on you.

370
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:34,560
It’s good that you’re here.

371
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,600
Let’s go grab something to eat.

372
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,480
The senior said they will buy me shaved ice.

373
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:52,520
Ouch. My stomach hurts.

374
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,440
I need to go to the bathroom.

375
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:03,600
It looks good on you.

376
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,400
What’s wrong?

377
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,680
Don’t you have to hurry back
to talk to the senior?

378
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,400
What are you doing?

379
00:24:57,520 --> 00:24:58,880
Listen to your heartbeat.

380
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,560
No, stop it.

381
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:26,760
I heard it.

382
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,160
You are jealous, aren’t you?

383
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:31,480
Jealous?!

384
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,720
That’s nonsense.

385
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,000
Are you jealous?

386
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:38,960
No.

387
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,080
You are definitely jealous.

388
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,920
What if I am?

389
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,080
Why are you smiling?

390
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:55,880
This is cute.

391
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:02,040
I don’t want to feel this way.

392
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,000
But I can’t help it.

393
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,160
So I don’t know how to tell you.

394
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,040
This is your dream.

395
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,800
I don’t want to bother you.

396
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:11,760
I…

397
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:18,640
When I was in the group,
I felt like I didn’t belong there.

398
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,520
I’m acting like a jerk.

399
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,240
You’re not a jerk, Orange.

400
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:30,680
I get it.

401
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:32,560
I really do.

402
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:44,680
I’m sorry.

403
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:53,840
This is the first time
that Boss Ko said he’s sorry.

404
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:57,880
So what?

405
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:01,120
It doesn’t mean you can do anything.

406
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:06,240
I will keep an eye on you 24/7.

407
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:06,920
Okay?

408
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:10,040
If you’re going to do that,
why don’t you move in with me?

409
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:12,440
That’s a bit much.

410
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,560
Excuse me. My name is A.

411
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:22,440
I think you have a unique face.

412
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,480
Are you interested in
being a photoshoot model?

413
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,880
Who are you talking to?

414
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:30,240
You.

415
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:31,720
What’s your name?

416
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,480
Ko Neung.

417
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:35,360
I’m Ko.

418
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:38,480
Your name is mod.

419
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,280
My name is Ko, not Mod.

420
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,760
You are also funny.

421
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,520
But…

422
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:48,360
Who are you?

423
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:52,560
In a simple word, I’m a talent scout.

424
00:27:52,720 --> 00:28:00,120
I go to schools and scout good-looking teens
to work as models or celebrities.

425
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,360
I see.

426
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,720
Can we trust him?

427
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,720
Do you want my business card?

428
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:12,280
Here.

429
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:20,480
I’m looking for a model to shoot
a cover of a teen fashion magazine.

430
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:22,240
I’ll give you 3,000 baht as your fee.

431
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,520
Damn, 3,000 baht.

432
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:26,560
You don’t need to agree right now.

433
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:29,120
You can go back
and talk to your parents first.

434
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:30,680
You can call me later.

435
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:33,320
I really like your face.

436
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,160
I’ve got to go back to Bangkok now.

437
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,960
I’ll be looking forward to your call.

438
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:38,840
Bye.

439
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:40,120
Goodbye.

440
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,120
What should I do?

441
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:44,000
He doesn’t seem like a bad guy.

442
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:46,440
He will give me 3,000 baht.

443
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:48,920
Do you want to do it because of the money
or because you want to be a model?

444
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:50,440
Both.

445
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:52,120
Ko.

446
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:54,360
Come here.

447
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:56,600
I’ve got to go.

448
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:00,160
Ko.

449
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:07,000
I’m keeping an eye on you, Dr. Glasses.

450
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,120
It’s been three days.

451
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:57,400
Have you called him?

452
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:00,320
No.

453
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,280
But my parents said I should give it a try.

454
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,560
Do it.

455
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,120
If it’s what you like, I’ll support you.

456
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:09,680
Is my boyfriend going to become a celebrity?

457
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,320
You’ve been teasing me a lot lately.

458
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,600
You should go back to study.

459
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:19,320
If you don’t get in med school,
I’ll laugh at you.

460
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,440
You are mean.

461
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,160
Are you sick?

462
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,800
I feel a bit feverish.

463
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:39,120
You should take medicine.

464
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,000
I will before going to bed.

465
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,760
Are you sure
you can go to school tomorrow?

466
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:48,320
No problem.

467
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,160
If you can’t, just tell me.

468
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,600
I’ll take leave to be with you.

469
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,920
No. Stop it.

470
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:17,960
What should I do with A Supajee?

471
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:26,120
It’s your home.

472
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,400
Can’t we go for another lap?

473
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,800
I don’t want to go home yet.

474
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,240
Stop being clingy.

475
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:43,240
You are all grown-up, aren’t you?

476
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:46,680
So you didn’t call to tell me
when you would be home.

477
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:48,760
My phone battery is dead.

478
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:53,760
Hello, Mom.

479
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:54,880
Hello.

480
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,760
Are you Augar?

481
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:58,680
I remember you.

482
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:00,680
Yes, I’m on my way home.

483
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,920
So I gave him a ride.

484
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:03,520
Thank you.

485
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:06,880
Since you gave him a ride,
why don’t you join us for dinner?

486
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:16,760
If you say no,
I won’t let you give him a ride again.

487
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:19,400
Yes.

488
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:23,720
What do we have for dinner?

489
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,720
I prepared your favorite dishes.

490
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:27,120
Really?

491
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:27,600
Yes.

492
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:33,480
Enjoy the meal.

493
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:35,120
Yes.

494
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:39,240
How do you know me?

495
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:45,040
When I go to pick Achi up at school,
I always see you with him.

496
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:47,920
I just didn’t get out of the car to meet you.

497
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:49,520
Is that so?

498
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:51,960
I didn’t know that.

499
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:59,840
One more thing,
Achi tells me everything about you.

500
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:04,640
Everything?

501
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:05,560
Yes.

502
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:13,480
Recently, you went on a trip together.

503
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:16,600
He also told me everything about the trip.

504
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:26,880
Right.

505
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,120
Are you…

506
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,040
I’m not mad at you.

507
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:32,000
I get it.

508
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,840
It’s not strange.

509
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:37,200
The faucet can be broken anytime.

510
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:44,400
But I have something to ask you.

511
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,160
You need to be honest with me.

512
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:49,080
Yes.

513
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:56,800
Do you know who sent this postcard?

514
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:59,720
I found it when I was cleaning his room.

515
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,760
Mom, what are you doing?

516
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:04,800
Why did you go into my room?

517
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:08,320
Let me mess up your hair, little boy.

518
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,480
Mom.

519
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:15,480
Is my son seeing someone?

520
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,360
Mom.

521
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:22,320
Let me mess up your hair, little boy.

522
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:24,360
Mom, stop it. Give it to me.

523
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:27,560
Who calls my son ‘little boy’?

524
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,560
Little boy.

525
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,560
Stop it.

526
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:43,160
See you.

527
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,200
Good night, Augar.

528
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:46,280
See you, little boy.

529
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:50,000
My mom might see it.

530
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:15,640
Ko.

531
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:17,760
Ko Song.

532
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,200
Ko Song.

533
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:25,000
Hello, Dad.

534
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:25,960
Hello.

535
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:31,720
I just talked to him on the phone.

536
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,440
He said I could come in.

537
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:34,720
Come in.

538
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:35,880
He’s upstairs.

539
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:37,280
Yes, Dad.

540
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:44,760
Dad.

541
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,680
Have you checked on Ko Song?

542
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:50,960
I just got back from work.

543
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:51,720
Why?

544
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,840
He was sick.

545
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:56,600
But he said he feels better now.

546
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,280
Can you come here? I want to talk to you.

547
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:01,120
Yes.

548
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:15,040
During the past two years,
I have had a problem at work.

549
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:18,600
Ko’s mom and I have talked.

550
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:21,440
She has to move back
to take care of her mother.

551
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:25,360
His grandmother is not doing well.

552
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:28,680
Thank you for keeping him company.

553
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,240
Yes, Dad.

554
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:37,000
Don’t worry.

555
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:40,800
My friends and I will take good care of him.

556
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:47,560
I don’t even know that my son was sick.

557
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,400
I don’t have time for him.

558
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,400
I hope you will visit him often.

559
00:36:59,360 --> 00:36:59,920
Yes, Dad.

560
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,400
You can go now.

561
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,320
Dad.

562
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:18,920
Maybe he just wants a quick chat with you.

563
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:22,720
How are you?

564
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,560
Are you tired from studying?

565
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,600
Have you eaten anything?

566
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:33,440
It doesn’t take long
to ask him these questions.

567
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:37,520
I’ll go upstairs now.

568
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:02,680
You go back to studying
right after you feel better.

569
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,600
You are very diligent, Doctor.

570
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:06,760
I saw the light in your room
has been turned off for a while.

571
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:07,760
Why did you take so long to come here?

572
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:10,360
My mom was telling me about a soap opera.

573
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:13,200
Are you bored?c

574
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:14,880
No.

575
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,320
Can we talk?

576
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:19,960
Sure.

577
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,000
Ko Song.

578
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:41,080
Yes.

579
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:48,080
After we graduate from high school,
will you leave me?

580
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:00,200
Will you go to a college far away from here?

581
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:09,320
Will we still get to see each other?

582
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,360
Orange.

583
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,440
Just thinking that

584
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:22,080
we won’t get to talk often like this,
it already makes me feel sad.

585
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:26,720
it already makes me feel sad.

586
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:37,520
It’s okay.

587
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:40,120
I promise that we will get to see each other.

588
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:52,400
If we attend different schools,
it will be hard for us to see each other.

589
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:05,680
If that’s the case,
I’ll try to make time to see you.

590
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:08,520
Ko Song.

591
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:14,120
I promise I won’t miss our meeting.

592
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:19,360
You don’t need to promise me that.

593
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:21,120
No, I want to.

594
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,480
Because I want to see you too.

595
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:29,520
If we don’t have many chances
to talk like this,

596
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,200
it also makes me sad.

597
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:00,760
Ko Song.

598
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,400
What are you doing?

599
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:14,960
What is this? Let me go.

600
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:15,960
You’re so stubborn.

601
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:18,920
Stop thinking about us being apart.

602
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:22,280
Ko Song, let me go.

603
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:27,760
Even though we like different things,
it doesn’t mean we will go separate ways.

604
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:30,800
Don’t argue with me.

605
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:33,280
If you do, I’ll kiss you.

606
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,880
But I want to argue back.

607
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:01,000
What did you say?

608
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,160
No. I’m just kidding.

609
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:08,440
(I heard from an adult
that the first time will help us grow up.)

610
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:13,480
(I think these words are not only for kids.)

611
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:16,200
(But it can apply to every phase of our life.)

612
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:18,720
[THE 10-FINALIST QUALIFYING ROUND
OF DRAGON BALL ULTIMATE FAN]

613
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:21,120
(We all have our first time.)
[THE 10-FINALIST QUALIFYING ROUND
OF DRAGON BALL ULTIMATE FAN]

614
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:31,840
(August didn’t pass the qualifying round
and didn’t get to appear on the show.)

615
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:39,000
It’s okay.

616
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:41,120
I’ll buy you an ice cream.

617
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:44,120
Come on.

618
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:48,800
Damn. Thawan Obkit.

619
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:50,800
Achi, I got on the team.

620
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:56,800
(Augar passed the tryout
for the national youth team.)

621
00:42:57,040 --> 00:42:58,320
(He made the team.)

622
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:07,640
So the person who sent you this postcard
is Augar, right?

623
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:11,800
(Achi opens up with his mom and
tells her that the postcard is from Augar.)

624
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:15,760
Achi, you can date anyone that you want.

625
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:17,720
I just want you to be honest with me.

626
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:27,040
(Ko Song’s Dad has breakfast
with Ko Song on Monday.)

627
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:28,600
Ko.

628
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:29,840
Let’s have breakfast together.

629
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:43,280
(I, the Orangeman,
get to do something new.)

630
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:47,760
His look can go well with many styles.

631
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:04,120
Augar, August, Achi.

632
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:05,640
Ko Neung.

633
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:06,960
Boss Ko.

634
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:10,120
I have something to show you.

635
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,360
What is it?

636
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:15,320
Here.

637
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:17,160
Damn. You look so good.

638
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:18,960
You look so good, Ko.

639
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:19,960
What do you think?

640
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:21,200
Open it.

641
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:22,000
Let me see.

642
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:24,960
Damn.

643
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:25,360
Look.

644
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,920
(Thank you for every first time in our life.)

645
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:40,560
(It helps us grow up.)

646
00:44:52,360 --> 00:44:53,600
- Why do we have to grow up?

647
00:44:57,360 --> 00:44:58,320
- Damn.

648
00:44:58,320 --> 00:44:59,720
- August, you made it.

649
00:44:59,720 --> 00:45:00,800
- This is how life is.

650
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,520
- We each need to follow our own path to grow.

651
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:07,520
- In your future, will I be a part of it?

652
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:11,080
- No matter where you and I go, we will never be apart.

653
00:45:14,720 --> 00:45:15,760
- Can you do that, Ko Song?

